[http://www.registeredcommons.org/ Registered Commons] takes the process of licensing creative works, anything covered by copyright, one step further by allowing individuals to securely register their authorship. 

URL = http://www.registeredcommons.org/

=Description=

At registration time the type of license that is applied to the work, such as [[Creative Commons]] or [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/GNU GNU] for example, can also be recorded and hence it is made clear who can use the work and in what circumstances.

[http://www.registeredcommons.org/ Registered Commons] can't guarantee protection however they undertake to maintain the time-stamp for 35 years and store the [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hash_code hash code] (a small digital "fingerprint") for at least 7 years all of which could help support an individual's claim to their work.

As [[Lessig, Lawrence|Lawrence Lessig]], founder of [http://creativecommons.org/ Creative Commons], said about Registered Commons:

:''“I think this will be extremely useful. You guys took something we did, and you added to it in a way that will really add important value and really make the copyright system - in a way that it should - work much better.”''


